jchrest.lib

Class ListPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • jchrest.lib.Pattern
      • jchrest.lib.ListPattern
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<PrimitivePattern>

    public class ListPattern
extends Pattern
implements java.lang.Iterable<PrimitivePattern>
    The ListPattern is the primary datatype used to represent compound patterns within Chrest. A ListPattern holds an ordered list of instances of other pattern types. The ListPattern may optionally indicate that it cannot be extended by setting the _finished flag. Note that once a pattern is 'finished', it cannot be added to. TODO: Think about if ListPatterns can be embedded within ListPatterns - would have to look inside ListPattern to make the match.

      • matches

        public boolean matches(Pattern pattern)
        Determines whether #this and the pattern specified match.
        Specified by:
        matches in class Pattern
        Parameters:
        pattern -
        Returns:
        If the following conditions all evaluate to Boolean.TRUE then Boolean.TRUE is returned. Otherwise, Boolean.FALSE is returned:
        • pattern is also a ListPattern
        • Invoking getModality() on #this and pattern returns the same Modality.
        • If #this is "finished":
          • The same value for size() must be returned when it is invoked on #this and pattern.
          • pattern must also be "finished"
        • If #this is not "finished" the value for size() must be less than or equal to the result for this method when invoked in context of pattern.
        • The ordering of PrimitivePatterns in #this must match the ordering of PrimitivePatterns in pattern.
